TestLink 1.5.1 - ReadMe

1. Introduction
===============================================================
TestLink is a web based test management and test execution system.
    It enables quality assurance teams to create and manage their test cases
    as well as to organize them into test plans. These test plans allow team
    members to execute test cases and track test results dynamically.TestLink is a GPL licensed open
    source project. All of the source code behind TestLink is freely available
    for download via SourceForge at http://www.sourceforge.net.If you are interested in contributing to the TestLink effort feel
    free to contact us.

2. System Requirements and Installation
===============================================================
TestLink environment includes PHP4, MySQL and a Web-server (e.g.
    functional WAMP installation).Download: You can get the newest version at sourceforge.net at https://sourceforge.net/projects/testlink/.Installation, update and configuration is described in Installation
    and Configuration manual  at http://testlink.sourceforge.net/docs/documents/installation.html . The procedure for TL 1.5.1 is
    identical as for TL 1.5.0.Update from TestLink 1.5.0: Database requires no change. Just unpack
    and configure this new release.

3. Release notes TestLink 1.5.1
===============================================================
This release is only a bug fixing release for
    TestLink 1.5.0.See CHANGELOG for more information about new
    features, bug fixes and changes.

4. Known problems
===============================================================
There are known issues:
      
        No blocking issue is known at the time.
      

      
        Several small issues is listed in SourceForge: Bugs.
      
    

5. Bug Reports and Feedback
===============================================================
The Bug Overview on the TestLink web site lets you search for and
    examine existing bug reports, submit your own bug reports, and tell us
    which bug fixes matter most to you.To submit a bug or a feature, please use our 
    Mantis installation at http://www.testlink.org/mantis/ for TestLinkFor historical reasons you can still look to existing bugs at
    SourceForge at https://sourceforge.net/tracker/?group_id=90976&atid=595494For the same reason you can browse the existing REF's at 
    SourceForge at https://sourceforge.net/tracker/?group_id=90976&atid=595497You may also contact us at the TestLink forum at http://www.testlink.org/tiki/tiki-forums.php
    .